defaultMifalot
default operates a number of programs focused on peace and coexistence. The goal of these programs is to bring together 
defaultdifferent groups within the
default diverse population
defaults in Israel and in the region including Jordan and Palestine. With all of these groups 
defaultfootball 
defaultb
defaultecomes a tool for bridging
default social, religious and ethnic divides. Football 
defaultis
default the common ground that all people like and relate to. It helps individuals from opposing groups realize that they are not so different. From there, we use this common ground to ho
defaultld a dialogue about differences
default, coexistence, conflict mitigation
default and how to understand and accept each other.
defaultMifalot's projects include the following:
default-
default 
defaultKnow Your Neighbor/Neighbor's United: Breaking down stereotypes and building trust - both on and off
default the field - between youth from different groups within Israel and between Israelis, Palestinians and Jordanians.
default-
default 
defaultCoaches for Social Change: Educating Palestinian and Israeli young adults together to be football coaches and peace educators and then sendi
defaultng them out into their communities to work as coaches with teams of youth.
